This paper deals with tracking and analyzing large-scale video remix in real-world events using visual memes and statistical models. The paper involves developing scalable detection algorithms, modeling content interactions on YouTube, and building predictive models for meme popularity. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Multimedia (cs.MM), followed by Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves statistical modeling (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques, which are also relevant to the research.
